end-good.narrative:
The function now reads:

function processOrder(userId, itemList, discountCode) {
  const user = getUser(userId);
  const total = calculateTotal(itemList);
  const discount = getDiscount(discountCode);
  const amount = total - (total * discount.percent / 100) + shippingCost(user.address);
  return chargeUser(user.paymentMethod, amount);
}

A $100 order with 20% off: 100 - (100 * 20/100) + shipping = $80 + shipping. The next developer can review this code in seconds.
